message.content: This question involves understanding the concept of balanced forces. If two students of equal strength pull a double-sided cup in opposite directions, the forces exerted on the cup will be equal and opposite. According to Newton's first law of motion, an object at rest will remain at rest unless acted upon by an unbalanced force. In this case, since the forces are balanced, the cup will remain stationary. Option (B) and (D) suggests that one student will be able to take the cup, which is not the case if they have equal strength.
